The course introduces students:
1)	nowadays Slavic world and Slavonic languages
2)	the problems of genesis of Slavonic languages and nations
3)	the ancient life of Slavic people ( habitat, social structures, beliefs) and sources which can lead to knowledge about ancient Slavs
4)	history of Slavonic philologyObjectives/eesmärkid:  An introduction to the Slavic Philology.  The first part introduces the history and development of this branch of knowledge. There are characterized nowadays broadcast area of Slavonic languages, introduced the problems of Slavs genesis and their life in the past. On the language base it is shown how the problems of Slavs genesis and evolution of Slavonic languages and nations are solved.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The students who have passed the studies: 1)	Own information about position of Slavonic languages nowadays in the world, know about the genesis of Slavs. 2)	Know about the study methods of national lingual-ethnic development. 3)	Know about the historical and nowadays broadcast area of Slavonic languages  4)	Able to distinguish between truth and speculative information  about the Slavs derivation and broadcast area. 5)	Have an eye for history of Slavonic philology, e.g. development in the history of Tartu slavistic.
